<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Color and pilosity. Head dorsally and ventrally dark brown. Antennae pale brown, with segment I dark yellow on basal 1/4; rostrum yellow, except segment IV dark brown. Eyes red. Anterior 1/3 of pronotum yellow. Connexiva and legs yellow. Prosternum yellow. Venter of abdomen dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,432,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Macropterous male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[446,570,476,501]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 10–15. 10" captionStart-1="FIGURES 16–19. 16" captionStartId-0="5.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox-0="[181,1403,236,1713]" captionTargetBox-1="[217,1381,224,1842]" captionTargetId-0="figure-106@5.[151,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetId-1="figure-81@6.[180,1408,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionText-0="FIGURES 10–15. 10. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, pronotum, dorsal view. Scale 0.05 mm. 11. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, prosternum, ventral view. Scale 0.05 mm. 12. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, dorsal view. Scale 0.10 mm. 13. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm. 14. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, right paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm. 15. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, left paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 16–19. 16. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, fore wing. Scale 0.25 mm. 17. Microvelia piedrancha, 17a. Macropterous male, fore tibia, 17b. Macropterous female, fore femur and tibia, arrow shows setae. Scale 0.025 mm. 18. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, middle tibia. Scale 0.025 mm. 19. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271492" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271498" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5271492/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5271498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 10–18</figureCitation>
) BL: 2.48; HL: 0.32; HW: 0.50; ANT I–IV: 0.16, 0.18, 0.22, 0.30; INT: 0.26; EYE: 0.14; 
<collectionCode box="[284,321,512,535]" country="Czech Republic" name="Západoceské muzeum v Plzni" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" type="Museum">PL</collectionCode>
: 0.72; 
<collectionCode box="[395,440,512,535]" country="Thailand" name="Paleontological Collections" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">PW</collectionCode>
: 0.90; FORELEG: FEM: 0.48, TIB: 0.38, TAR I: 0.26; MIDLEG: FEM: 0.52, TIB: 0.48, TAR I: 0.12, TAR II: 0.20; HINDLEG: FEM: 0.70, TIB: 0.74, TAR I: 0.14, TAR II: 0.20.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Antennomere I thickest, curved outward, II widening to apex, 
<collectionCode box="[975,1003,584,607]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">III</collectionCode>
cylindrical, IV fusiform. Pronotum completely covering meso- and metanotum; anterior part with centrally interrupted transversal row of punctuations near anterior margin; distinctly foveate, with pits more numerous on posterior 2/3; without longitudinal median carina (
<figureCitation box="[236,322,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15. 10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,236,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-106@5.[151,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. 10. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, pronotum, dorsal view. Scale 0.05 mm. 11. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, prosternum, ventral view. Scale 0.05 mm. 12. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, dorsal view. Scale 0.10 mm. 13. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm. 14. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, right paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm. 15. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, left paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271492/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); humeral angles prominent and truncate, apex produced to a broadly rounded angle. Prosternum scattered foveate (
<figureCitation box="[355,436,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15. 10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,236,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-106@5.[151,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. 10. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, pronotum, dorsal view. Scale 0.05 mm. 11. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, prosternum, ventral view. Scale 0.05 mm. 12. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, dorsal view. Scale 0.10 mm. 13. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm. 14. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, right paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm. 15. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, left paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271492/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Connexival segments angled upward at 45º. Last abdominal tergite subquadrate, with posterior margin slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[258,342,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15. 10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,236,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-106@5.[151,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. 10. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, pronotum, dorsal view. Scale 0.05 mm. 11. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, prosternum, ventral view. Scale 0.05 mm. 12. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, dorsal view. Scale 0.10 mm. 13. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm. 14. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, right paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm. 15. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, left paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271492/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Genital segment I projecting onto posterolateral angles with apex triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1314,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15. 10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,236,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-106@5.[151,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. 10. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, pronotum, dorsal view. Scale 0.05 mm. 11. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, prosternum, ventral view. Scale 0.05 mm. 12. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, dorsal view. Scale 0.10 mm. 13. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm. 14. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, right paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm. 15. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, left paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271492/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of last abdominal sternite broadly concave (
<figureCitation box="[785,877,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15. 10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,236,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-106@5.[151,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. 10. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, pronotum, dorsal view. Scale 0.05 mm. 11. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, prosternum, ventral view. Scale 0.05 mm. 12. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, dorsal view. Scale 0.10 mm. 13. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm. 14. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, right paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm. 15. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, left paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271492/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Venter of genital segment I projecting onto posterolateral angles and with apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[673,759,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–15. 10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,236,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-106@5.[151,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. 10. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, pronotum, dorsal view. Scale 0.05 mm. 11. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, prosternum, ventral view. Scale 0.05 mm. 12. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, dorsal view. Scale 0.10 mm. 13. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm. 14. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, right paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm. 15. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, left paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271492/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Parameres asymmetrical, elongate, strongly curved (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10–15. 10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,236,1713]" captionTargetId="figure-106@5.[151,1436,193,1741]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–15. 10. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, pronotum, dorsal view. Scale 0.05 mm. 11. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, prosternum, ventral view. Scale 0.05 mm. 12. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, dorsal view. Scale 0.10 mm. 13. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm. 14. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, right paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm. 15. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, left paramere. a, lateroventral view; b, lateral view. Scale 0.025 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271492/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Figs. 14, 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Wings surpassing genital segments, bearing seven irregular whitish maculae (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1230,943,968]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19. 16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[217,1381,224,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-81@6.[180,1408,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. 16. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, fore wing. Scale 0.25 mm. 17. Microvelia piedrancha, 17a. Macropterous male, fore tibia, 17b. Macropterous female, fore femur and tibia, arrow shows setae. Scale 0.025 mm. 18. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, middle tibia. Scale 0.025 mm. 19. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). All tibiae with grooming structures at apices (
<figureCitation box="[496,633,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19. 16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[217,1381,224,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-81@6.[180,1408,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. 16. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, fore wing. Scale 0.25 mm. 17. Microvelia piedrancha, 17a. Macropterous male, fore tibia, 17b. Macropterous female, fore femur and tibia, arrow shows setae. Scale 0.025 mm. 18. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, middle tibia. Scale 0.025 mm. 19. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Figs. 17, 18</figureCitation>
). Fore tibia with slightly prolonged apical lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1269,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19. 16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[217,1381,224,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-81@6.[180,1408,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. 16. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, fore wing. Scale 0.25 mm. 17. Microvelia piedrancha, 17a. Macropterous male, fore tibia, 17b. Macropterous female, fore femur and tibia, arrow shows setae. Scale 0.025 mm. 18. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, middle tibia. Scale 0.025 mm. 19. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 17a</figureCitation>
) and bearing a row of short, stout setae similar to spines near outer margin of apex, visible only at 400X (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1329,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19. 16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[217,1381,224,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-81@6.[180,1408,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. 16. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, fore wing. Scale 0.25 mm. 17. Microvelia piedrancha, 17a. Macropterous male, fore tibia, 17b. Macropterous female, fore femur and tibia, arrow shows setae. Scale 0.025 mm. 18. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, middle tibia. Scale 0.025 mm. 19. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 17b</figureCitation>
); lacking grasping comb. Middle tibia with seven fine, long, pale setae on apical 1/3. (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1091,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19. 16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[217,1381,224,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-81@6.[180,1408,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. 16. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, fore wing. Scale 0.25 mm. 17. Microvelia piedrancha, 17a. Macropterous male, fore tibia, 17b. Macropterous female, fore femur and tibia, arrow shows setae. Scale 0.025 mm. 18. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, middle tibia. Scale 0.025 mm. 19. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,464,1087,1112]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" reason="1">Macropterous female.</emphasis>
BL: 2.16; HL: 0.30; HW: 0.48; ANT I–IV: 0.18, 0.18, 0.22, 0.34; INT: 0.26; EYE: 0.12; 
<collectionCode box="[215,252,1124,1147]" country="Czech Republic" name="Západoceské muzeum v Plzni" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" type="Museum">PL</collectionCode>
: 0.70; 
<collectionCode box="[327,372,1124,1147]" country="Thailand" name="Paleontological Collections" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">PW</collectionCode>
: 0.86; FORELEG: FEM: 0.42, TIB: 0.32, TAR I: 0.20; MIDLEG: FEM: 0.52, TIB: 0.44, TAR I: 0.10, TAR II: 0.18; HINDLEG: FEM: 0.60, TIB: 0.70, TAR I: 0.14, TAR II: 0.20.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
Smaller and thinner than male. Structures of legs similar to male, except fore tibia without prolonged apical lobe (
<figureCitation box="[215,313,1231,1256]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19. 16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[217,1381,224,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-81@6.[180,1408,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. 16. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, fore wing. Scale 0.25 mm. 17. Microvelia piedrancha, 17a. Macropterous male, fore tibia, 17b. Macropterous female, fore femur and tibia, arrow shows setae. Scale 0.025 mm. 18. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, middle tibia. Scale 0.025 mm. 19. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 17b</figureCitation>
). Margins of connexival segments I– 
<collectionCode box="[729,757,1232,1255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">III</collectionCode>
subparallel, margins of connexival segments IV–VII angled upward at 60º and convergent caudad. Posterior margin of last abdominal sternite straight (
<figureCitation box="[1218,1305,1268,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19. 16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[217,1381,224,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-81@6.[180,1408,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. 16. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, fore wing. Scale 0.25 mm. 17. Microvelia piedrancha, 17a. Macropterous male, fore tibia, 17b. Macropterous female, fore femur and tibia, arrow shows setae. Scale 0.025 mm. 18. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, middle tibia. Scale 0.025 mm. 19. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Venter of genital segment I projecting onto posterolateral angles and bearing one oval, shining black macula on anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[245,328,1340,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19. 16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[217,1381,224,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-81@6.[180,1408,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. 16. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous male, fore wing. Scale 0.25 mm. 17. Microvelia piedrancha, 17a. Macropterous male, fore tibia, 17b. Macropterous female, fore femur and tibia, arrow shows setae. Scale 0.025 mm. 18. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, middle tibia. Scale 0.025 mm. 19. Microvelia piedrancha, macropterous female, apex of abdomen, ventral view. Scale 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5271498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5271498/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,433,1375,1400]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" reason="1">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Padilla-Gil &amp; Moreira, 2013" authorityName="Padilla-Gil &amp; Moreira" authorityYear="2013" box="[441,698,1376,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piedrancha" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[441,698,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Microvelia piedrancha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[706,771,1375,1400]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[706,771,1375,1400]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is structurally similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Drake &amp; Roze, 1958" authorityName="Drake &amp; Roze" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="timida">
<emphasis box="[1056,1258,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Microvelia timida</emphasis>
Drake &amp; Roze, 1958
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[289,408,1412,1437]" name="Venezuela" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. However, the latter is smaller, possesses a fore tibial grasping comb in both males and females; and has segment I of the antenna longer than segment II.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,1509]" box="[199,1295,1484,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1484,1509]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
Collected on the surface of slow flowing water covered by abundant floating vegetation.
</paragraph>
